HEADWORD: Epistrophe
<hw>E*pis"tro*phe</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., from
Gr. <?/ a turning toward, return, fr. <?/ to turn toward;
<grk>'epi`</grk> upon, to + <?/ to turn.]</ety> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld>
<def>A figure in which successive clauses end with the same word or
affirmation; <it>e. g.</it>, ⟦ldquo⟧Are they Hebrews? <xex>so am
I</xex>. Are they Israelites? <xex>so am I</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧</def> <rj><au>2
Cor. xi. 22.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epistyle</ent>⟦br⟧
